00:08:21.120 --> 00:08:22.620
Now, the author had a bunch of ideas,

00:08:22.620 --> 00:08:24.330
but the three that really stood out to me

00:08:24.330 --> 00:08:27.210
were characters, culture, and technology

00:08:27.210 --> 00:08:29.730
because these also kept
coming up in my Twitter DMs.

00:08:29.730 --> 00:08:33.450
So let's test them out one by
one, starting with characters.

00:08:33.450 --> 00:08:35.250
Did you know that Japanese characters

00:08:35.250 --> 00:08:36.990
are literally built different?

00:08:36.990 --> 00:08:39.450
You see, Chinese, Japanese,
and Korean writing systems

00:08:39.450 --> 00:08:41.760
share a bunch of logographic characters.

00:08:41.760 --> 00:08:44.880
These are individual symbols
that represent whole words.

00:08:44.880 --> 00:08:48.270
The sheer amount of these
CJK characters in existence

00:08:48.270 --> 00:08:50.940
lead to massive font file sizes.

00:08:50.940 --> 00:08:53.940
For comparison, this is a font
that's designed to support

00:08:53.940 --> 00:08:57.120
Greek, Cyrillic, and
Latin-based writing systems.

00:08:57.120 --> 00:08:59.700
It contains less than 4,000 glyphs.

00:08:59.700 --> 00:09:02.640
That's typography speak for a
representation of a character.

00:09:02.640 --> 00:09:04.110
These are three different glyphs.

00:09:04.110 --> 00:09:05.820
Now let's look at a font that supports

00:09:05.820 --> 00:09:07.140
all of those languages

00:09:07.140 --> 00:09:10.500
as well as Chinese, Japanese, and Korean.

00:09:10.500 --> 00:09:11.333
Keep in mind,

00:09:11.333 --> 00:09:14.610
these writing systems do
not have capital letters.

00:09:14.610 --> 00:09:16.170
It's so much more.

00:09:16.170 --> 00:09:17.850
So this means that Japanese websites

00:09:17.850 --> 00:09:20.010
have significantly fewer font options,

00:09:20.010 --> 00:09:22.740
since not many designers want
to take on this challenge.

00:09:22.740 --> 00:09:25.320
The fonts that do exist might
load in a little more slowly

00:09:25.320 --> 00:09:26.700
compared to other writing systems

00:09:26.700 --> 00:09:29.250
since they're pulling from
libraries that are massive.

00:09:29.250 --> 00:09:31.140
And finally, that lack of capitalization

00:09:31.140 --> 00:09:32.940
means that graphic designers lose a tool

00:09:32.940 --> 00:09:34.560
for creating visual hierarchy.

00:09:34.560 --> 00:09:36.480
These are all factors
that could realistically

00:09:36.480 --> 00:09:38.640
cause design differences between regions

00:09:38.640 --> 00:09:42.270
that use CJK characters
and the rest of the world,

00:09:42.270 --> 00:09:44.370
except it doesn't.

00:09:44.370 --> 00:09:47.460
From what I found, other
regions that use CJK characters

00:09:47.460 --> 00:09:50.130
don't exhibit the same
design patterns as Japan.

00:09:50.130 --> 00:09:53.460
So we learned something
interesting, which is useless.

00:09:53.460 --> 00:09:55.620
Put that on my tombstone.

00:09:55.620 --> 00:09:56.550
Anyway.

00:09:56.550 --> 00:09:57.570
But what about culture?

00:09:57.570 --> 00:09:59.790
This was a tricky one
because I was a STEM student,

00:09:59.790 --> 00:10:01.920
so I don't have a lot of the
domain knowledge necessary

00:10:01.920 --> 00:10:05.430
to accurately identify and
compare global cultures.

00:10:05.430 --> 00:10:07.950
However, being a STEM student also means

00:10:07.950 --> 00:10:10.260
that that didn't stop me from trying.

00:10:10.260 --> 00:10:12.357
I started off by using
geographic proximity,

00:10:12.357 --> 00:10:13.290
but that failed.

00:10:13.290 --> 00:10:15.570
So then I used a binary identifier

00:10:15.570 --> 00:10:17.490
for if a country was
part of the global north

00:10:17.490 --> 00:10:18.540
or global south.

00:10:18.540 --> 00:10:19.530
Also no pattern.

00:10:19.530 --> 00:10:20.363
But like I said,

00:10:20.363 --> 00:10:22.740
I don't know if this is the
best way to compare cultures.

00:10:22.740 --> 00:10:24.510
However, given what I've found,

00:10:24.510 --> 00:10:26.610
I'm just not convinced that culture

00:10:26.610 --> 00:10:29.610
is the primary cause of
Japan's unique web design.

00:10:29.610 --> 00:10:31.710
Thus, all we're left with is technology.

00:10:31.710 --> 00:10:33.360
How hardware and software

00:10:33.360 --> 00:10:35.640
shape the way websites are designed today

00:10:35.640 --> 00:10:38.310
and why Japan didn't follow that path.

00:10:38.310 --> 00:10:40.800
So let's start from the beginning

00:10:40.800 --> 00:10:43.230
and go on a journey through time.

00:10:43.230 --> 00:10:44.430
The worldwide web is invented

00:10:44.430 --> 00:10:45.810
as a way for nerds to share documents,

00:10:45.810 --> 00:10:48.120
which is why every
website looked like this.

00:10:48.120 --> 00:10:48.953
Not good.

00:10:48.953 --> 00:10:50.790
But the people knew it
could be so much more.

00:10:50.790 --> 00:10:54.150
It could share ideas, house
businesses, share pictures of...

00:10:54.150 --> 00:10:57.600
At a whopping 0.05 megabits per second,

00:10:57.600 --> 00:10:59.220
the average person could access

00:10:59.220 --> 00:11:03.570
a whole new world of
information pixel by pixel,

00:11:03.570 --> 00:11:05.520
but that didn't stop people
from enjoying the internet.

00:11:05.520 --> 00:11:06.750
I mean, if you don't know any better,

00:11:06.750 --> 00:11:08.550
I guess it's not its own circle of hell.

00:11:08.550 --> 00:11:11.070
However, the internet takes off.

00:11:11.070 --> 00:11:11.970
In just two years,

00:11:11.970 --> 00:11:14.850
we go from 2000 websites to over a million

00:11:14.850 --> 00:11:16.770
with no signs of slowing down.

00:11:16.770 --> 00:11:19.290
Scripting languages make
websites more interactive,

00:11:19.290 --> 00:11:20.310
almost too interactive.

00:11:20.310 --> 00:11:21.960
This is the internet.
I'm not here to interact.

00:11:21.960 --> 00:11:24.450
And Flash gave designers so much freedom

00:11:24.450 --> 00:11:27.450
and gave children so many iconic games.

00:11:27.450 --> 00:11:29.490
The question wasn't what can we do,

00:11:29.490 --> 00:11:31.623
it was what can't we do?

00:11:32.490 --> 00:11:33.450
And sure, if you were using

00:11:33.450 --> 00:11:34.980
the wrong browser or browser version,

00:11:34.980 --> 00:11:36.570
some websites might not work,

00:11:36.570 --> 00:11:39.510
but when they did, it was glorious.

00:11:39.510 --> 00:11:41.610
So why don't websites
look like this anymore?

00:11:41.610 --> 00:11:44.730
Why aren't they diverse
and chaotic and beautiful?

00:11:44.730 --> 00:11:46.140
Well, two reasons.

00:11:46.140 --> 00:11:48.720
One, a lot of those 90s
websites were unstable,

00:11:48.720 --> 00:11:50.310
unsecure, and inaccessible.

00:11:50.310 --> 00:11:52.140
So standards were established
to make sure websites

00:11:52.140 --> 00:11:56.190
use the same building blocks
and, two, search engines.

00:11:56.190 --> 00:11:58.380
While early search
engines used information

00:11:58.380 --> 00:12:01.590
submitted or curated by
webmasters and web users,

00:12:01.590 --> 00:12:03.150
they evolved to use bots

00:12:03.150 --> 00:12:05.610
that crawled the internet,
scraped information,

00:12:05.610 --> 00:12:07.380
and informed search results.

00:12:07.380 --> 00:12:09.000
Initially, search engines just checked

00:12:09.000 --> 00:12:11.640
if a website's contents
contained search terms,

00:12:11.640 --> 00:12:14.070
but then webmasters just
started spamming key terms

00:12:14.070 --> 00:12:15.570
to get to the top of search results.

00:12:15.570 --> 00:12:17.760
So then search engines started valuing

00:12:17.760 --> 00:12:20.760
how often a website is
referenced by other websites.

00:12:20.760 --> 00:12:22.380
But then companies started paying

00:12:22.380 --> 00:12:24.870
to be linked on random websites

00:12:24.870 --> 00:12:26.550
to get to the top of search results.

00:12:26.550 --> 00:12:28.740
This cycle continued until eventually

00:12:28.740 --> 00:12:32.070
search engines became so
powerful and so sophisticated

00:12:32.070 --> 00:12:34.950
that websites had no choice
but to play by the rules.

00:12:34.950 --> 00:12:36.930
Web design became more
structured and uniform

00:12:36.930 --> 00:12:39.720
to make it easier for
search engines to find them.

00:12:39.720 --> 00:12:41.310
Now, you might think that the differences

00:12:41.310 --> 00:12:42.660
in how search engines work

00:12:42.660 --> 00:12:46.020
is what caused websites to look
different around the world,

00:12:46.020 --> 00:12:48.990
except Google is basically
the only search engine

00:12:48.990 --> 00:12:51.120
and it's been that way since 2005.

00:12:51.120 --> 00:12:52.380
In every country except China,

00:12:52.380 --> 00:12:54.930
websites would wanna
optimize for Google search.

00:12:54.930 --> 00:12:56.880
So what else could have
caused Japanese web design

00:12:56.880 --> 00:12:57.900
to fracture off?

00:12:57.900 --> 00:12:59.580
Well, we need to consider this.

00:12:59.580 --> 00:13:01.500
The rise of smartphones.

00:13:01.500 --> 00:13:03.933
It's 2007, and suddenly
all of these websites

00:13:03.933 --> 00:13:06.060
that were designed for desktop viewing

00:13:06.060 --> 00:13:08.670
are too difficult to navigate
on small phone screens

00:13:08.670 --> 00:13:11.550
and too data-heavy to
load on limited plans.

00:13:11.550 --> 00:13:12.600
- You know, you can help me out,

00:13:12.600 --> 00:13:15.060
if you're on wifi, if
you could just get off.

00:13:15.060 --> 00:13:17.910
- The easy answer was to
start simplifying navigation,

00:13:17.910 --> 00:13:21.090
reducing content, making things bigger.

00:13:21.090 --> 00:13:23.460
This all resulted in
this minimalist design

00:13:23.460 --> 00:13:26.850
that we're all familiar
with, that we call modern.

00:13:26.850 --> 00:13:29.340
So it seems like it
wasn't language or culture

00:13:29.340 --> 00:13:30.810
that caused Japan's web design

00:13:30.810 --> 00:13:32.850
to fracture off from
the rest of the world.

00:13:32.850 --> 00:13:34.380
Instead, it's that their websites

00:13:34.380 --> 00:13:38.130
never adopted the practices
for mobile-friendly web design.

00:13:38.130 --> 00:13:39.420
But why?

00:13:39.420 --> 00:13:41.910
And that's because the
Japanese smartphone revolution

00:13:41.910 --> 00:13:44.610
happened about 10 years
before the rest of the world.

00:13:44.610 --> 00:13:49.610
Their phones had email in '99,
cameras in 2000, 3G by 2001.

00:13:50.490 --> 00:13:52.620
They were so far ahead
of the rest of the world,

00:13:52.620 --> 00:13:55.500
but domestic companies didn't
feel the need to spread abroad

00:13:55.500 --> 00:13:58.380
because they were already
profitable enough in Japan.

00:13:58.380 --> 00:14:01.410
But when the Western web began
simplifying for the iPhone,

00:14:01.410 --> 00:14:03.450
Japanese web designers
didn't need to do that

00:14:03.450 --> 00:14:06.690
because Japanese people
weren't using the iPhone.

00:14:06.690 --> 00:14:08.250
Now, there are a couple of other reasons

00:14:08.250 --> 00:14:10.410
like risk aversion that
might influence this,

00:14:10.410 --> 00:14:11.490
but it really seems

00:14:11.490 --> 00:14:13.710
like Japan's relationship with technology,

00:14:13.710 --> 00:14:15.600
specifically outdated technology,

00:14:15.600 --> 00:14:18.780
is the main reason why Japanese
internet looks so different.

00:14:18.780 --> 00:14:20.730
And after looking at thousands of websites

00:14:20.730 --> 00:14:22.560
and learning the history of the internet,

00:14:22.560 --> 00:14:25.770
I realized that this
isn't just fun trivia.

00:14:25.770 --> 00:14:28.170
This is relevant to us even
if you're not in Japan,

00:14:28.170 --> 00:14:31.050
even if you never intend to
go to a Japanese website,

00:14:31.050 --> 00:14:32.880
because these websites are artifacts

00:14:32.880 --> 00:14:34.950
of how hardware and software,

00:14:34.950 --> 00:14:36.930
the infrastructure of the internet

00:14:36.930 --> 00:14:40.260
tangibly shapes the way
we consume information.

00:14:40.260 --> 00:14:43.530
I can't process this because
I don't read Japanese.

00:14:43.530 --> 00:14:46.470
But similarly, I get overwhelmed
when looking at old Reddit.

00:14:46.470 --> 00:14:48.420
The small images, the amount of text,

00:14:48.420 --> 00:14:49.770
it's hard for me to understand

00:14:49.770 --> 00:14:51.390
because I'm not used to to it.

00:14:51.390 --> 00:14:53.850
Now, I want you to think about
today's web technologies.

00:14:53.850 --> 00:14:56.850
Infinite scrolling,
algorithmically selected content,

00:14:56.850 --> 00:14:58.860
cuts every two seconds.

00:14:58.860 --> 00:15:00.090
I'm not saying it's good or bad,

00:15:00.090 --> 00:15:02.880
but it sure as heck seems
like it can impact us.

00:15:02.880 --> 00:15:03.750
And with the internet

00:15:03.750 --> 00:15:06.483
constantly in our pockets or our hands,

00:15:07.320 --> 00:15:09.510
it can shape the way we see the world.

00:15:09.510 --> 00:15:11.460
Yes, I'm just saying the
medium is the message.

00:15:11.460 --> 00:15:14.193
But either way, have a lovely day.

